    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="62"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1894</hi>
                        </date>. (Received July 14.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 246.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your telegram of the 6th instant, with regard to the refunding of certain duties
                    collected by the Government of Brazil on wheat flour.</p>
                <p>I have brought this matter to the attention of the Government, as directed, and
                    am awaiting a reply.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thos. L. Thompson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
